<paper id="1502991851"><title>Deciding Probabilistic Bisimilarity Over Infinite-State Probabilistic Systems</title><year>2004</year><authors><author org="Masaryk University" id="2172233494">Tomáš Brázdil</author><author org="Masaryk University" id="1845058341">Antonín Kučera</author><author org="Masaryk University" id="331121140">Oldřich Stražovský</author></authors><n_citation>5</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1489359924</reference><reference>1497670448</reference><reference>1511105469</reference><reference>1525935082</reference><reference>1561838634</reference><reference>1561934984</reference><reference>1601373402</reference><reference>1793726001</reference><reference>1944241544</reference><reference>1972203711</reference><reference>1976268573</reference><reference>1986669897</reference><reference>2005998857</reference><reference>2006889545</reference><reference>2096610849</reference><reference>2098543914</reference><reference>2106934908</reference><reference>2153983552</reference><reference>2167246417</reference><reference>2168605507</reference><reference>2764296810</reference></references><venue id="1145706541" type="C">International Conference on Concurrency Theory</venue><doi>10.1007/978-3-540-28644-8_13</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.44548">Discrete mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.44001">Combinatorics</keyword><keyword weight="0.40948">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.64714">Probabilistic CTL</keyword><keyword weight="0.478">Finite-state machine</keyword><keyword weight="0.61524">Probabilistic analysis of algorithms</keyword><keyword weight="0.52352">Decidability</keyword><keyword weight="0.51571">Pushdown automaton</keyword><keyword weight="0.59164">Probabilistic logic</keyword><keyword weight="0.48607">Time complexity</keyword><keyword weight="0.48068">Bounded function</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>We prove that probabilistic bisimilarity is decidable over probabilistic extensions of BPA and BPP processes. For normed subclasses of probabilistic BPA and BPP processes we obtain polynomial-time algorithms. Further, we show that probabilistic bisimilarity between probabilistic pushdown automata and finite-state systems is decidable in exponential time. If the number of control states in PDA is bounded by a fixed constant, then the algorithm needs only polynomial time.</abstract></paper>